{
  "signal_description": "Retrieve the following information from the 'defaultview-545' table: 'Vendor Number', 'Company Code Name', 'No. of Invoices paid late', 'Invoice Amount paid late', 'Posted as Overdue', 'Short Payment Terms', and 'High Rework Rate'. The 'Vendor Number' is derived from the 'PO Item Supplier ID' column, and the 'Company Code Name' is derived from the 'Accounting Company Code' column. The 'Invoice Amount paid late' is the sum of the 'Last Invoice Item Amount' column, and the 'No. of Invoices paid late' is the count of the 'Last Invoice Id' column. The 'Short Payment Terms' is the count of 'Last Invoice Id' where the 'Last Invoice Due Date' is less than the 'Last Invoice Payment Date' and the difference between the 'Last Invoice Due Date' and 'Last Invoice Accounting Date' is less than 7 days. The 'Posted as Overdue' is the count of 'Last Invoice Id' where the 'Last Invoice Payment Date' is null and the 'Last Invoice Due Date' is less than the current date. The 'High Rework Rate' is the count of 'Last Invoice Id' where the 'Last Invoice Due Date' is less than the 'Last Invoice Payment Date' and there is at least one occurrence of an event other than 'Receive PO Item'. The results are ordered by the 'Vendor Number' and 'Invoice Amount paid late'."
}
